{
  "stem": "22086.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- I didn't, but my husband's family had a plan that we're gonna go in to the Rowne ghetto, and we'll stay there and see what's gonna happen.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It took us a couple days, because we traveled to in-- at night.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you had to try to get into the city where nobody will see you.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when we did come into the city, we had to go into the-- I forgot the word-- to the camp, you know, that we had in Rowne to the ghetto, that we shouldn't be seen.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you are just as afraid of Jewish people that, you know, might not want you there, that they-- they always were afraid that outsiders would start trouble or do harm for them.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so you had to go in and try to mix in with the crowd, without being noticed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We took a couple days, and we were-- I think, one night-- it was the second night when we were in the city, that we got in, and the following day we went to work with everybody.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, to-- to a place where they took us in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That mean we had people that we knew, and they took us in.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You were trying to hide in the field, under the straw, under bushes, under whatever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Whatever we could get on the road.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A lot of times, at night, we would stop in some kind of village and knock on a door and ask for bread, for food.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sometimes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sometimes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes, but you couldn't stay there because there were incidents that, when you ask for food, they'll give it to you, but they'll send the authorities on you.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So you had take and go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also, a lot of people in one room.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
